	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100745457610443>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=100745457610443>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100745457610443>A Different Strategy</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100745457610443#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Dec 4th 3:29 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=124743><span id= >Aeterna</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Here is a fun and effective strategy a friend taught me.&nbsp;&nbsp;Get in a group with another chanter, 3 wizzies (mages can work too) and a cleric. i did this in lguk, just a good place for this strategy. heres what you do: fear one mob, let it go and find some friends. will pull back a ton of mobs if lucky, keep mezzin the ones that come till you are sure that all are there. then someone gives a cue, in my case it was &quot;FIRE&quot; and the two chanters start chain casting the 2 stun spells, while the nukers chain cast their aoe dds and cleric group heals when needed if anyone gets bashed on. so we died a few times... but its fun imo, and you can actually rake in a lotta exp if you do it right! i have heard of people takin out near 50 mobs at once doin this, i dont know that first hand though =) <br><br>Aeterna Sedai<br>38 Chanter on Povar<br>Kindred Honour<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Dec  4 03:31:04 2001</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
