	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=100686385416261>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100686385416261>Chain pulling Enchanter</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100686385416261#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Nov 27th 7:24 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=118851><span id= >kpak</span></a><br><span id=notbold>81 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I was wondering if everyone knew the power of a good enchanter.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ok, everyone knows us as traffic cop, Eq's verion of drug dealers, ect.. Well the enchanter class can be a bit more.  If done properly, we can be group PLing gods, LOL.  Here is what i do for it, find a open minded group full with the right class, at least 2 tanks, a cleric, a sowing class (at later levels rangers are awsome cuz they can sow, and do damage melee at the same time), and the last another class that can do some serious damage in a short amount of time, ie monk, rogue, wiz, mage.  Here is the spells you need loaded, a color series (preferably two, with the 3 sec stun) a mez spell, youre tash spell, and whatever you want to use in the other slots.  You have the sower sow ya, and then you go to work.  Run around and look for a target (one that you know can be mezzed without much resistence).  From a safe distance tash it, run back to group, stop for a second so youre mez spell wont be interupted, Mez, and have everyone else go to work.  Then you go out and find next poor unlucky creaure, dont go too far cuz you wont recieve xp if the mob gets killed too fast, bring back to camp and mez it while the group is beating on the first.  Sit and med, when the first one is killed, group starts on the second. Then you go out and look for another, and repeat above process.  If you get a resist on mez, either cast it again (since all mez spells has a short cst time) or color it with 3 sec stun and cast mez again.  It is very important that you build cha, instead of int as soon as possible so youre mez does not get resisted as much.  Anyways, ive been doing this since lvl 23 at LOIO and all the way up to lvl 36 in OT.  I hear this is really easy in DL and most outside area because you will not get as many adds as you will in dungeons.  Doing this will get you a lot of friends, and will make leveling a cinch (I leveled from 27-28 in like 4 hours at Sarnark Fort in LOIO, and all pulls where about 5 lvls lower than me so each kills did not give me that much xp).  Hopefully this helps =)<br><br>Aflack Dukky<br>Saryn </p>&nbsp;<br>Sage Aflack Dukky<br>65 Coercer<br>Saryrn Server<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479240" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479240</a></td></td></tr>
