	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100524402984455>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=100524402984455>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100524402984455>RE: New characters</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100524402984455#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Nov 8th 1:27 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>202 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, you bring up some good points here Boxo, but I will have to disagree with you on some issues.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm not one to flame, but if there is incorrect or even questionable information out there, I don't want it being believed as 'gospel truth.'  OK, so much for the disclaimer ...<br><br>1) Yes, if you choose a religion you will make your life much more difficult as an enchanter.  The only reason I could give for choosing to have a religion is for roleplaying or if you just want some extra challenge.<br><br>2) The INT/CHA debate has been going for a long time and will continue to be an issue with enchanters.  Higher charisma does seem to have at least some effect on the success rate of landing mezz and charm spells, especially on higher conning MOBs.  What it does NOT affect is the duration of these spells.  This said, an argument can be made for keeping int and cha both balanced, or even favoring charisma over intelligence if you do a lot of charming.  As far as soloing goes, charm soloing can efficient both in regards to mana and experience if done correctly.  The idea of getting full experience for two or more MOBs in one battle gives a good reason for soloing a chanter at least some of the time.<br><br>3) Many people claim that you need both intelligence and wisdom for learning tradeskills.  This is again a long-standing EQ debate and by no means a solved one.  The argument states that intelligence affects your chance of improving the skill while wisdom affects the chances that you will succeed in the combination.  I have seen posts stating that the EQ developers themselves admitted that both factors (chance of success and chance of improvement) will be based on the higher of either wisdom or intelligence.  So, unless they are lying, there is no reason for an enchanter to worry about wisdom at all.<br><br>4)  Agree for the most part.  ;)<br><br>5)  Agree 100%<br><br>6)  Also agree.  You will get people who offer you donations after shooting a clarity their way, personally I'll accept it but some people will refuse all donations.<br><br>Boxo, this post was in no way meant to discredit you or your attempts to educate the young'ns, but I think some of the things you brought up as 'fact' or 'truth' are up for debate at the very least.<br><br>OK, I'll stop here and let the replies come flowing.  At least this may start some new discussions and/or threads on this board.  It's been pretty dead lately.<br><br>-Yizzelar<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
