	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>On the subject of charisma versus intelligence I would like to throw in my 2 cp. I put almost all of my bonus points (High Elf Enchanter) into charisma based on a suggestion I received from a high level enchanter. His point was that the gear which boosts intelligence is far superior (albeit far more expensive) to charisma gear. +7 charisma bracelets are nice but where's the AC? HPs? Other bonuses? The point is that at level 30 I can max out at 190 Int and 173 Cha and I guarantee that my HP, AC, and several other stats are higher because of the intelligence gear I have acquired. It seems that putting points into charisma instead of intelligence can be considered as an investment for the future. While the lower intelligence may be a detriment in the earlier levels, it can be overcome as you advance and gain wealth.<br>On the subject of the importance of charisma, there is no definitive yes or no, despite what the "experts" say. It is my opinion that charisma does have an effect on mezzing and charming but that the main factor is the level of your opponent. I have noticed a better success rate with a higher charisma with both spells on black, yellow, and red cons but little or no improvement on blue or green cons. EQ is a game of subtleties and sometimes life or death can come down to one spell being resisted. If a high charisma means one more spell out of twenty sticks, then imho it's worth it.<br><br>Volarious Fizznott &lt;Concordium Discors&gt;<br>30th Level High Elf Enchanter<br>Torvo</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
